An E6B flight computer is traditionally an analog device resembling a combination slide rule and slide wheel that performs calculations specific to aviation. For example, an E6B can be used to calculate heading and groundspeed after taking into account forecast winds. It performs all of the steps to correct your observation, find GP of the object, do the sight reduction, and plot the LOP.  No steps are skipped and all details are shown.  Click where the LOPs cross in the plot and you have found your fix!

Besides finding your fix, ezAlmanacOne is one of the best tools available to perform compass checks from a bearing observation of one of the navigational bodies.
